In this article, the White House Press Secretary issues a statement congratulating Julia Gillard on becoming the Prime Minister of Australia and the first female prime minister in the country's history. The statement highlights the special relationship and alliance between the United States and Australia, expressing confidence that it will continue to thrive under Gillard's leadership. President Obama looks forward to working with Gillard on various issues of cooperation and plans to speak with her soon. The President also expresses gratitude to former Prime Minister Kevin Rudd and extends his best wishes to him.